HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES, October 2, 2025.
The committee on Education, to whom were referred the petition
(accompanied by bill, House, No. 672) of Edward R. Philips that the
Department of Elementary and Secondary Education be authorized to
offer two hours of evidence based in-service suicide awareness and
prevention training once every other year to certain employees and the
petition (accompanied by bill, House, No. 699) of Danillo A. Sena and
others for legislation to strengthen suicide prevention in schools, reports
recommending that the accompanying bill (House, No. 4563) ought to
pass.
For the committee,
KENNETH I. GORDON.

